# Code to calculate Mean Rating Comparison + Gap Analysis - showing HOW MUCH RATINGS DIFFER FOR EACH ATTRIBUTE
product_cols = [
    'seat_comfort',
    'leg_room_service',
    'food_and_drink',
    'inflight_entertainment',
    'inflight_wifi_service',
    'cleanliness',
    'products_rating_score',
    'products_rating_percentage'
]
service_cols = [
    'on_board_service',
    'inflight_service',
    'checkin_service',
    'online_boarding',
    'ease_of_online_booking',
    'baggage_handling',
    'gate_location',
    'departure_arrival_time_convenience',
    'services_rating_score',
    'services_rating_percentage'
]

satisfied = df[df['satisfaction_bool'] == True]
unsatisfied = df[df['satisfaction_bool'] == False]
def rating_comparison(df_sat, df_unsat, columns):
    comparison = pd.DataFrame({
        'Satisfied_Mean': df_sat[columns].mean(),
        'Unsatisfied_Mean': df_unsat[columns].mean()
    })
    comparison['Gap'] = comparison['Satisfied_Mean'] - comparison['Unsatisfied_Mean']
    return comparison.sort_values('Gap', ascending=False)

# Statistical Significance - independent T test
'''
Rule of thumb:
p < 0.05  Statistically significant difference
p  0.05  Difference not reliable
'''

from scipy.stats import ttest_ind

def ttest_analysis(df_sat, df_unsat, columns):
    results = []
    for col in columns:
        t_stat, p_val = ttest_ind(
            df_sat[col].dropna(),
            df_unsat[col].dropna(),
            equal_var=False
        )
        results.append([col, t_stat, p_val])
        
    return pd.DataFrame(
        results,
        columns=['Attribute', 'T-Statistic', 'P-Value']
    ).sort_values('P-Value')

product_ttest = ttest_analysis(satisfied, unsatisfied, product_cols)
service_ttest = ttest_analysis(satisfied, unsatisfied, service_cols)

product_ttest, service_ttest

# Ranked Diverging Charts
'''
Executives instantly see where unsatisfied customers rate badly and how far satisfied customers pull away.
'''

def plot_diverging_bar(comparison_df, title):
    df = comparison_df.sort_values('Gap')

    y = np.arange(len(df))

    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))

    plt.barh(y, df['Satisfied_Mean'], label='Satisfied', alpha=0.8)
    plt.barh(y, -df['Unsatisfied_Mean'], label='Unsatisfied', alpha=0.8)

    plt.yticks(y, df.index)
    plt.axvline(0, color='black', linewidth=1)
    plt.xlabel('Average Rating')
    plt.title(title)
    plt.legend()
    plt.tight_layout()
    plt.show()
    
plot_diverging_bar(product_comparison, 'Product Attributes: Satisfied vs Unsatisfied Ratings')
plot_diverging_bar(service_comparison, 'Service Attributes: Satisfied vs Unsatisfied Ratings')

def plot_gap_annotated(comparison_df, title, save_path):
    df = comparison_df.sort_values('Gap', ascending=True)

    plt.figure(figsize=(9, 6))
    bars = plt.barh(df.index, df['Gap'])

    for bar in bars:
        width = bar.get_width()
        plt.text(width + 0.02, bar.get_y() + bar.get_height()/2,
                 f'{width:.2f}', va='center')

    plt.title(title)
    plt.xlabel('Rating Gap (Satisfied  Unsatisfied)')
    plt.tight_layout()
    plt.savefig(save_path, dpi=300, bbox_inches='tight')
    plt.show()
    print(f"Chart saved as: {save_path}")

plot_gap_annotated(product_comparison, 'Product Attributes: Satisfaction Gap',
                   save_path='plot_gap_annotated_product.png')
plot_gap_annotated(service_comparison, 'Service Attributes: Satisfaction Gap',
                   save_path='plot_gap_annotated_service.png')

def plot_dumbbell(comparison_df, title, save_path):
    df = comparison_df.sort_values('Gap')

    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    
    plt.hlines(
        y=df.index,
        xmin=df['Unsatisfied_Mean'],
        xmax=df['Satisfied_Mean'],
        color='gray',
        linewidth=2
    )
    
    plt.plot(df['Unsatisfied_Mean'], df.index, 'o', label='Unsatisfied')
    plt.plot(df['Satisfied_Mean'], df.index, 'o', label='Satisfied')
    
    plt.xlabel('Average Rating')
    plt.title(title)
    plt.legend()
    plt.tight_layout()
    plt.savefig(save_path, dpi=300, bbox_inches='tight')
    plt.show()
    print(f"Chart saved as: {save_path}")

plot_dumbbell(product_comparison, 'Product Attributes: Rating Comparison', 
              save_path='dumbell_plot_chart_product_comparison.png')
plot_dumbbell(service_comparison, 'Service Attributes: Rating Comparison', 
              save_path='dumbell_plot_chart_service_comparison.png')

# Combined Chart
'''
Attributes highlighted in red show the highest satisfaction gaps and are the strongest drivers of dissatisfaction.
Yellow attributes moderately influence satisfaction, while green attributes represent hygiene factors with limited differentiation power.
'''

def combined_impact_chart(product_df, service_df, save_path='satisfaction_impact_analysis.png'):
    # Combine product and service attributes
    combined = pd.concat([
        product_df.assign(Category='Product'),
        service_df.assign(Category='Service')
    ])

    # Sort by impact
    combined = combined.sort_values('Gap')

    # Impact levels
    conditions = [
        combined['Gap'] >= 1.2,
        (combined['Gap'] >= 0.6) & (combined['Gap'] < 1.2),
        combined['Gap'] < 0.6
    ]
    colors = np.select(
        conditions,
        ['#d62728', '#ffbf00', '#2ca02c'],  # red, yellow, green
        default='#2ca02c'
    )

    # Plot
    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 8))
    bars = plt.barh(combined.index, combined['Gap'], color=colors)

    # Annotate values
    for bar in bars:
        width = bar.get_width()
        plt.text(width + 0.03, bar.get_y() + bar.get_height()/2,
                 f'{width:.2f}', va='center')

    # Labels & title
    plt.xlabel('Rating Gap (Satisfied  Unsatisfied)')
    plt.title('Customer Satisfaction Impact Analysis\n(Products & Services Combined)')

    # Legend
    from matplotlib.patches import Patch
    legend_elements = [
        Patch(facecolor='#d62728', label='High Impact'),
        Patch(facecolor='#ffbf00', label='Medium Impact'),
        Patch(facecolor='#2ca02c', label='Low Impact')
    ]
    plt.legend(handles=legend_elements, title='Impact Level')

    plt.tight_layout()

    # Save & show
    plt.savefig(save_path, dpi=300, bbox_inches='tight')
    plt.show()

    print(f"Chart saved as: {save_path}")

combined_impact_chart(
    product_comparison,
    service_comparison,
    save_path='combined_chart_customer_satisfaction_impact.png'
)

# Code to calculate Delay Impact Ratio

delay_thresholds = [0, 15, 30, 45, 60]
results = []

for threshold in delay_thresholds:
    if threshold == 0:
        # On-time arrivals
        mask = df['arrival_delay_in_minutes'] == 0
        label = 'On-time (0 min)'
    else:
        # Delayed arrivals
        mask = df['arrival_delay_in_minutes'] >= threshold
        label = f'{threshold} min'
    
    subset = df[mask]
    if len(subset) > 0:
        satisfaction_rate = (subset['satisfaction_bool'].sum() / len(subset)) * 100
        results.append({
            'Delay_Category': label,
            'Total_Customers': len(subset),
            'Satisfaction_Rate': round(satisfaction_rate, 2)
        })

# Create table
delay_df = pd.DataFrame(results)
print("Delay Impact Ratio Table:")
print(delay_df.to_string(index=False))

# Create graph
plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
bars = plt.bar(delay_df['Delay_Category'], delay_df['Satisfaction_Rate'], color='steelblue')
plt.xlabel('Arrival Delay Category')
plt.ylabel('Satisfaction Rate (%)')
plt.title('Impact of Arrival Delays on Satisfaction Rate')
plt.ylim(0, 100)

# Add value labels
for bar in bars:
    height = bar.get_height()
    plt.text(bar.get_x() + bar.get_width()/2., height + 1,
             f'{height}%', ha='center', va='bottom')

plt.tight_layout()
plt.savefig('delay_impact_ratio_0_15min_30min_.png', dpi=300, bbox_inches='tight')
plt.show()

# Filter dissatisfied high value customers

target_customers = df[(df['customer_value'] == 'high') & (~df['satisfaction_bool'])]

product_cols = ['seat_comfort', 'leg_room_service', 'food_and_drink', 
                'inflight_entertainment', 'inflight_wifi_service', 'cleanliness']

                'online_boarding', 'ease_of_online_booking', 'baggage_handling',
                'gate_location', 'departure_arrival_time_convenience']

ax1.tick_params(axis='x', rotation=45)
